âOf course, Iâll go,â replied George Hay to someoneâs inquiry.

âIâm too seedy,â continued Bobby, who had not spared the punch.

âI, too,â added Oliver.

âI should like to, but I darenât,â chimed in Polly.  And so a detachment
was added to the contingent that were piloted by the irrepressible Coney.

Bobby during the past night had, alas! not followed the paths of
