the recipe is happily lostâfailed to assist his jaded appetite; alongside
him stood a huge tankard of âcup,â and pouring out a gobletful for his
newly-found chum, and gulping down a pint by way of introduction, he
gasped: âBy Gad, old man, Iâm dâ glad to see you!  To begin with, you
must dine with me at 8âhere.  Iâve asked Prince Hohenlohe and Baron
Spaum, and young Beust and Count Adelberg, and if youâll swear on a sack
of bibles not to repeat it, I expect two live Ambassadorsâitâs always as
wellâ (he continued in a confidential tone) âto have a sacred person or
two handy in case of a row with the police.  First we go to Endell
Streetâto Faultlessâs pit.  Iâve got a match for a monkey with Hamilton
to beat his champion bird, The Sweep, and after that Iâve arranged with a
detective to take us the rounds in the Ratcliff Highway.  No dressing,
old man; the kit you came over in is the ticket, and a sovereign or two
