in every wrinkle of your personâwhy, if youâre dancing with a beauty
sheâll be going over you all the time.  I often used to laugh and shout
out, âGo it, Iâm not a bit ticklish!ââstill, what the hâ does it matter?â
And his lordship sucked down another libation to the gods.

âI suppose you can speak French or German; if not you can try Irishânot
that it matters, for I expect Fred Granville and Chuckle Saunders, and
Hamilton is sure to bring a mob, so I think we may count on having the
best of it if it comes to a row.  How long are you up for?  A month, eh?
Oh, well, then weâre right for the Derby, and Iâll tell you what weâll
do.  Weâll go down the evening beforeâthe night before the big race
